FBIS4-31039 "dreeu107_i_94002" FBIS-EEU-94-107 Daily Report 2 Jun 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Silajdzic Explains Absence Silajdzic Explains Absence AU0206141694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 2 Jun 94 AU0206141694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Text] As is known, negotiations on the cease-fire with the aggressor [word indistinct] called by Yasushi Akashi were supposed to be held in Geneva today. Our delegation has not gone to Geneva. The reasons are explained by Prime Minister Haris Silajdzic: [Begin Silajdzic recording] Considering [words indistinct] on the withdrawal of the Serbian aggressor soldiers from the 3 km zone in Gorazde has not been accomplished, we are still not going to Geneva to discuss the cease-fire. However, the peace talks that began in Talloires will continue on Saturday [4 June], the day after tomorrow. Regarding the negotiations that are continuing in Talloires, [words indistinct] but the negotiations on the cease-fire still cannot be held because [words indistinct] withdrawal from Gorazde [words indistinct].
